Are you familar with the UAV operation to exit?
To get famaliar with your UAV and know the basic flight knowledge and safely you must read the following content carefuly.
Altitude is limited to 50 meters, distance limited to 100 meters during beginner mode.
UAV is set to beginner mode by default, you can only turn off the beginner mode after you finish 300 minutes of flying.
Landing: Tap the landing button within the app
Preparation: Put the UAV on a flat surface, at least 5 meters away
Control: Use right stick to control the UAV to fly forward, backward, left or right
Take off: Tap the take-off button in the app.
Start motor: Pull left and right stick to Pigeon - toed position (see right picture) release the stick immediately after the motors start.
Emergency shutdown: Push the power button and auto take-off / land button for 5 seconds until you hear the beeping sound has stopped completely.
Stop the motor: Pull down the throttle to lowest and hold for 5 seconds, motor will then stop.
Open the landing gear and place the UAV on a flat surface.
Keep the tail towards you during take-off, landing and flight.
Battery side is the tail, the other end is the head
Stand at least 5 meters away from the UAV at all times.
Please fly in open and safe space.
Avoid obstacles such as crowds, high buildings, trees, high voltage transmission lines, signal towers etc.
Do not fly in rainy, windy or snowy weather.
